  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Left ventricular failure (LVF) is a common cause of acute exacerbation of chronic obstructive
      pulmonary disease (AECOPD).

      This association is frequently underestimated with regard to the difficulty of clinical
      diagnosis .

      The investigators expect that Valsalva Maneuver (VM) could be useful in this issue.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
